NOMAKHOSI Veronica Gans was convicted and sentenced by the Bloemfontein Magistrates’ Court on Thursday, 10 February, for fraud, forgery, contravention of the Estate Agency Affairs Act and money laundering. The 40-year-old’s conviction originates from an incident that took place in May 2017, where the victim deposited the money to Gans Property Investments for purchasing houses at Mafora in Bloemfontein. According to Captain Christopher Singo, Gans contacted the victim and indicated that properties at Mafora were no longer for sale and she would search for others. “The victim then told Gans that she was not interested in other properties. She then requested a refund of R175 000, that she had deposited to Gans Property Investment. “Gans then told the victim that her company was experiencing some financial difficulties, and she would refund the money at a later stage. After numerous follow-ups, no money was received by the victim,” Singo said in a statement. He added that the matter was reported to the Hawks in Bloemfontein for further investigation, that resulted in Gans being served with a summons on 12 June 2020. She appeared in court on several occasions, concluding to her conviction. “The court sentenced Gans to eight years imprisonment for fraud, suspended for five years on condition that she refunds the victim an amount of R175 000 on or before 31 December 2024,” Singo added. Gans also got a five-year suspended sentences for forgery, contravening the Estate Agency Affairs Act and money laundering.